Module uk.gov.gchq.eventlogging
Package event.logging

Class Email

  • java.lang.Object
    • event.logging.BaseObject
      • event.logging.Email
  • public class Email
extends BaseObject
    Describes an email sent from one user to one or more recipients.

    Java class for Email complex type.

    The following schema fragment specifies the expected content contained within this class. 

     <complexType name="Email">
   <complexContent>
     <extension base="{event-logging:3}BaseObject">
       <sequence>
         <element name="From" type="{event-logging:3}User" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="To" type="{event-logging:3}User" maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="Cc" type="{event-logging:3}User" maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="Bcc" type="{event-logging:3}User" maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="Subject" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}string" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="Content" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}string" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="MimeType" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}string" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="Date" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}string" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="Data" type="{event-logging:3}Data" maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0"/>
       </sequence>
     </extension>
   </complexContent>
 </complexType>

        public java.util.List<User> getTo()
        The user(s) and/or distribution group(s) that the email was sent to.

        Gets the value of the to property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the to property.

            getTo().add(newItem);

      • getDate

        public java.lang.String getDate()
        The date taken from the email 'Date' header. This date is in string form and in the format and timezone as produced by the email client. It may be local time or UTC depending on the client, therefore it may differ to the EventTime of this event. It is also possible it is invalid if the email client device is misconfigured, e.g. in the future.

        Gets the value of the date property.

        Returns:
        possible object is String
